The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for medical imaging, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The focus of the paper is on addressing the memory bottleneck in training these models, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of optimized hardware, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
